      <h1 class="f24 p8 pink">羽扇纶巾 <span class="f16 nor gray">yǔ sh&agrave;n guān jīn</span> <object classid="clsid:D27CDB6E-AE6D-11cf-96B8-444553540000" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=5,0,0,0" width="16" height="16" id="pronunciation"> <param name="movie" value="speaker.swf"></param> <param name="flashvars" value="sound_name=mp3/14/13151.mp3"></param> <param name="wmode" value="transparent"></param> <a href="mp3/14/13151.mp3"><img border="0" width="16" height="16" src="speaker.png" alt="羽扇纶巾发音" /></a> </object></h1> 
      <table align="center" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
       <tbody>
        <tr>
         <th width="60"></th>
         <td></td>
        </tr>
        <tr> 
         <th valign="top">成语解释</th>
         <td>拿着羽毛扇子，戴着青丝绶的头巾。形容态度从容。</td>
        </tr>
        <tr> 
         <th valign="top">成语出处</th>
         <td>宋 苏轼《念奴娇 赤壁怀古》词：“小乔初嫁了，雄姿英发。<strong class="f14 pink nor">羽扇纶巾</strong>，谈笑间，强虏灰飞烟灭。”</td>
        </tr>
        <tr> 
         <th valign="top">成语繁体</th>
         <td>羽]巾</td>
        </tr>
        <tr> 
         <th>成语简拼</th>
         <td>ysgj</td>
        </tr>
        <tr> 
         <th>成语注音</th>
         <td>ㄧㄩˇ ㄕㄢA ㄍㄨㄢ ㄐㄧㄣ</td>
        </tr>
        <tr> 
         <th>常用程度</th>
         <td>常用成语</td>
        </tr>
        <tr> 
         <th>感情色彩</th>
         <td>中性成语</td>
        </tr>
        <tr> 
         <th>成语用法</th>
         <td>联合式；作宾语、定语；形容态度从容</td>
        </tr>
        <tr> 
         <th>成语结构</th>
         <td><a href="?jiegou=1" class="f14">联合式成语</a></td>
        </tr>
        <tr> 
         <th>产生年代</th>
         <td>古代成语</td>
        </tr>
        <tr> 
         <th>近 义 词</th>
         <td><a href="?id=MTcwMQ==" class="f14" target="_blank">纶巾羽扇</a></td>
        </tr>
        <tr> 
         <th valign="top">成语例子</th>
         <td>章诒和《往事并不如烟&middot;君子之交》：“<strong class="f14 pink nor">羽扇纶巾</strong>饰卧龙，帐前四将镇威风。”</td>
        </tr>
        <tr> 
         <th>英语翻译</th>
         <td>waving a feather fan and wearing a kerchielf with a green silk ribbon</td>
        </tr>
